{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Cond"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Consider the following example of a shared variable.  One or more"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"threads can wait for data to be published to the variable and when"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"another thread publishes the data, it can signal one of the waiting","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"threads to wake up to collect the data."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is an example for using GCond to block a thread until a condition"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"is satisfied:","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(C Language Example):"}]},{"syntax":"C","code":["  gpointer current_data = NULL;","  GMutex data_mutex;","  GCond data_cond;","","  void","  push_data (gpointer data)","  {","    g_mutex_lock (&data_mutex);","    current_data = data;","    g_cond_signal (&data_cond);","    g_mutex_unlock (&data_mutex);","  }","","  gpointer","  pop_data (void)","  {","    gpointer data;","","    g_mutex_lock (&data_mutex);","    while (!current_data)","      g_cond_wait (&data_cond, &data_mutex);","    data = current_data;","    current_data = NULL;","    g_mutex_unlock (&data_mutex);","","    return data;","  }"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Whenever a thread calls "},{"code":"pop_data()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" now, it will wait until","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"current_data is non-","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", i.e. until some other thread","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"has called "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"push_data()"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The example shows that use of a condition variable must always be"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"paired with a mutex.  Without the use of a mutex, there would be a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"race between the check of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"current_data"},{"text":" by the while loop in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pop_data()"},{"text":" and waiting. Specifically, another thread could set","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"current_data","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" after the check, and signal the cond (with nobody"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"waiting on it) before the first thread goes to sleep. ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond"},{"text":" is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"specifically useful for its ability to release the mutex and go","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to sleep atomically."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is also important to use the "},{"code":"g_cond_wait()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"g_cond_wait_until()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"functions only inside a loop which checks for the condition to be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"true.  See ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_cond_wait()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for an explanation of why the condition may"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"not be true even after it returns.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If a ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" is allocated in static storage then it can be used"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"without initialisation.  Otherwise, you should call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_cond_init()"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"on it and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_cond_clear()"},{"type":"text","text":" when done."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","isActive":true},{"text":" should only be accessed via the g_cond_ functions.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond"},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as an owner of an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GCond"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It provides the methods that can operate on this data type through ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondProtocol","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" as a strong reference or owner of a "},{"code":"GCond","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":") for a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GCond"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"Note","type":"aside"}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"title":"Cond","symbolKind":"class","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Cond"}],"role":"symbol","externalID":"s:4GLib4CondC","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Cond","kind":"identifier"}],"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"roleHeading":"Class"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/cond"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond"},{"text":" struct is an opaque data structure that represents a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"condition. Threads can block on a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" if they find a certain"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"condition to be false. If other threads change the state of this"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"condition they signal the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", and that causes the waiting"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"threads to be woken up."}],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(_:)-3cuz9","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(_:)-3wkhq","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(_:)-46zzs","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(_:)-8cx4a","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(_:)-ewbk","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLi